{
  "stem": "15174.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She almost-- I mean here we were, and she was afraid that they were gonna send us back because we had-- we had exchanged comic books.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Well, we explained what we were doing and we got off.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We-- I mean we got out and we stayed with my great uncle and my great aunt for a month.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And now my father's brother, who-- whom my father had worked for in Germany was already in New York.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were living in Washington Heights at that time and-- and we were in Brooklyn.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And-- And my father couldn't find a job in New York.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we came to Buffalo because my-- my father's two sisters, both of whom had been in Cuba at the time the arrived there, and my cousin Edith who was the daughter of one of them, Frieda-- had moved-- had left Cuba.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had gotten a visa to the United States the year before and they had come to Buffalo because of some other relatives who lived there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, that's-- that's why you went to certain places.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You knew somebody.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You wanted to go someplace where you knew somebody and where you knew somebody might be able to help you.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we came to Buffalo.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was the end of July of 1942.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my-- my parents in their wisdom decided that what I needed was fresh air.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So three days after we arrived in Buffalo they sent me to the Jewish Fresh Air Camp, which was a terrible experience, because number one, I didn't speak English, so I couldn't communicate with anybody.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And two, I didn't know anybody.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
